      <div class="pf-alert" style="margin-top:2rem;">
        <strong>Checkatrade places the Wirral average at £4,000 to £6,000 for a 3-bed central heating installation. Our starting price of £3,500 is at the lower end of the Wirral market, with a written fixed-price quote from a free site survey and no surprises on invoice day.</strong>
        <p>The final price depends on property size, wall construction, floor type, boiler location and pipework complexity. No written quote is issued without a site visit. We visit your property, assess every factor and provide a price you can rely on.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>


  <!-- WIRRAL PROPERTY TYPE SECTION, UNIQUE -->
  <section class="pf-section" style="background:#f1f5f9;">
    <div class="container">
      <span class="pf-section-label">WIRRAL LOCAL KNOWLEDGE</span>
      <h2 style="text-align:center;">Every Wirral Property Needs a Different Heating System</h2>
      <p class="pf-sub">The Wirral has more property diversity than almost any Merseyside borough. A 1910 terrace in Birkenhead and a 1970s semi in Bebington and a 5-bed detached in Heswall are completely different installation challenges. Getting the system type right at survey stage prevents expensive problems later.</p>

      <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr;gap:1.5rem;margin-top:2rem;">

        <div class="pf-card pf-card-left-orange">
          <div style="display:flex;gap:1rem;align-items:flex-start;flex-wrap:wrap;">
            <div style="background:var(--orange);color:#fff;border-radius:6px;padding:0.3rem 0.75rem;font-family:'Barlow Condensed',sans-serif;font-weight:900;font-size:0.85rem;white-space:nowrap;flex-shrink:0;">CH41 CH42 CH44 CH45</div>
            <div>
              <strong style="display:block;color:var(--navy);font-size:1rem;margin-bottom:0.35rem;">Birkenhead, Rock Ferry, Wallasey and New Brighton. Terrace Properties. Combi or System.</strong>
              <p style="font-size:0.93rem;color:var(--muted);margin:0;line-height:1.65;">The Victorian and Edwardian terraces of CH41 to CH45 are some of the most common central heating installation jobs on the Wirral. Before recommending a combi boiler in these properties, we test mains water pressure at the free survey. Many older terraces in Birkenhead and Wallasey have mains pressure too low for a combi to deliver satisfactory hot water flow to an upstairs bathroom. In these cases a system boiler with a small unvented or vented cylinder is the correct solution. Fitting a combi in a low-pressure property is one of the most expensive installation mistakes. We never recommend a system type before testing the pressure.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="pf-card pf-card-left-orange">
          <div style="display:flex;gap:1rem;align-items:flex-start;flex-wrap:wrap;">
            <div style="background:var(--orange);color:#fff;border-radius:6px;padding:0.3rem 0.75rem;font-family:'Barlow Condensed',sans-serif;font-weight:900;font-size:0.85rem;white-space:nowrap;flex-shrink:0;">CH47 CH48</div>
            <div>
              <strong style="display:block;color:var(--navy);font-size:1rem;margin-bottom:0.35rem;">Hoylake and West Kirby. Period Houses. Often Without Full Central Heating.</strong>
              <p style="font-size:0.93rem;color:var(--muted);margin:0;line-height:1.65;">West Kirby and Hoylake have a high proportion of period houses, many of which were either never centrally heated or have part systems that leave some rooms cold. These properties typically have solid brick walls and limited underfloor void access, both of which affect pipe routing. We assess every route at the free survey to avoid unnecessary damage to original features. Many West Kirby properties have good mains pressure and are well-suited to a system boiler with an unvented cylinder for multiple bathrooms at full mains pressure. We also advise on the most efficient boiler position for the property rather than defaulting to the existing boiler location.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="pf-card pf-card-left-orange">
          <div style="display:flex;gap:1rem;align-items:flex-start;flex-wrap:wrap;">
            <div style="background:var(--navy);color:#fff;border-radius:6px;padding:0.3rem 0.75rem;font-family:'Barlow Condensed',sans-serif;font-weight:900;font-size:0.85rem;white-space:nowrap;flex-shrink:0;">CH60 CH61 CH62 CH63 CH64</div>
            <div>
              <strong style="display:block;color:var(--navy);font-size:1rem;margin-bottom:0.35rem;">Heswall, Pensby, Bromborough and Neston. Larger Homes. System Boilers and Zone Control.</strong>
              <p style="font-size:0.93rem;color:var(--muted);margin:0;line-height:1.65;">The larger detached and semi-detached properties of south Wirral typically require a system boiler paired with a hot water cylinder, multi-zone heating and in many cases separate heating circuits for ground and first floor. These are not combi boiler installations. A system boiler setup for a 4-bed south Wirral property includes zone valves for separate upstairs and downstairs control, a smart multi-zone thermostat, a properly sized cylinder for multi-bathroom hot water demand and a full magnetic filtration setup. We design and install these systems regularly across CH60 to CH64. The free survey for larger Wirral properties takes longer and is more detailed, covering boiler sizing, zone design and cylinder specification.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="pf-card pf-card-left-orange">
          <div style="display:flex;gap:1rem;align-items:flex-start;flex-wrap:wrap;">
            <div style="background:#475569;color:#fff;border-radius:6px;padding:0.3rem 0.75rem;font-family:'Barlow Condensed',sans-serif;font-weight:900;font-size:0.85rem;white-space:nowrap;flex-shrink:0;">CH43 CH46 CH49</div>
            <div>
              <strong style="display:block;color:var(--navy);font-size:1rem;margin-bottom:0.35rem;">Prenton, Moreton and Upton. Mid-Century Housing. System Upgrades and Radiator Additions.</strong>
              <p style="font-size:0.93rem;color:var(--muted);margin:0;line-height:1.65;">The post-war semis and detached properties of central Wirral typically have existing central heating systems that are ageing or underperforming. A full system replacement is not always necessary. We assess at the free survey whether a new boiler with a power flush and radiator additions resolves the issues, or whether the full system needs replacing. Partial upgrades from £1,500 are often the right answer for these properties and represent better value than a full replacement of a structurally sound but underperforming system.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>


  <!-- SIGNS -->
  <section class="pf-section" style="background:#f8fafc;">
    <div class="container">
      <h2 style="text-align:center;">Signs Your Wirral Home Needs a Central Heating Upgrade</h2>
      <p class="pf-sub">These are the most common situations reported by Wirral homeowners before calling us for a free survey.</p>
      <div class="pf-signs" style="margin-top:2rem;">
        <div class="pf-sign"><div><strong>No central heating in your Wirral property</strong><p>A number of older Wirral properties, particularly in CH41, CH42 and coastal CH47 have never had central heating installed. A full system from £3,500 transforms the property and adds measurable value in the Wirral sales and rental market.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-sign"><div><strong>Some rooms always cold despite the heating being on</strong><p>Missing radiators, an undersized boiler or a poorly balanced system means heating can never keep pace. A free survey identifies whether a radiator addition, system balance or full upgrade resolves it.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-sign"><div><strong>System takes very long to warm up</strong><p>Sludge build-up, a failing pump or an undersized boiler for the property are the most common causes on older Wirral systems. We diagnose the root cause at the free survey before recommending a solution.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-sign"><div><strong>Cold spots on radiators that bleeding does not fix</strong><p>Cold at the bottom indicates sludge and magnetite. Cold at the top after bleeding indicates a flow problem. Persistent cold spots across the system suggest a power flush is needed before any new components are connected.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-sign"><div><strong>High bills with poor results across south Wirral larger homes</strong><p>An oversized property heated by an undersized or ageing boiler burns more gas for less heat. A new A-rated boiler with zone controls and properly balanced radiators typically reduces heating bills by 20 to 35%.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-sign"><div><strong>EPC rating of D, E, F or G</strong><p>A poor EPC rating on a Wirral property almost always indicates an inefficient heating system. A new installation is the single most impactful EPC improvement available and may qualify for ECO4 funding.</p></div></div>
      </div>
      <div style="background:#f97316;border-radius:10px;padding:1.5rem;text-align:center;margin-top:2rem;">
        <p style="color:#ffffff;font-weight:700;font-size:1rem;margin-bottom:0.75rem;">Book a free survey and we will tell you exactly what your Wirral home needs and give you a written fixed price.</p>
        <a href="tel:07399676656" class="btn btn-lg" style="background:#1a3a5c;color:#ffffff;box-shadow:0 4px 14px rgba(26,58,92,0.4);">CALL 07399 676656</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>


  <!-- WHAT IS INCLUDED -->
  <section class="pf-section" style="background:#f1f5f9;">
    <div class="container">
      <h2 style="text-align:center;">What Is Included in Your Wirral Central Heating Installation</h2>
      <p class="pf-sub">No hidden extras. Everything included in the price confirmed at your free survey.</p>
      <div class="pf-who-grid" style="margin-top:2rem;">
        <div class="pf-who-item pf-who-yes"><span class="pf-who-icon">✓</span><div><strong>New A-rated boiler correctly sized for your property</strong><p>Worcester Bosch, Vaillant, Ideal or Baxi. Combi or system boiler selected based on your mains pressure, number of bathrooms and property size, not defaulted to whatever is cheapest or easiest.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-who-item pf-who-yes"><span class="pf-who-icon">✓</span><div><strong>Full radiator set designed for each room</strong><p>We calculate the correct radiator output for every room based on size, insulation and heat loss. No guesswork, no undersized radiators in bedrooms that are always cold.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-who-item pf-who-yes"><span class="pf-who-icon">✓</span><div><strong>All pipework routed and fitted</strong><p>All pipe routes planned to minimise disruption to existing decoration. We work neatly and clean up fully at the end of every working day. In solid-wall Wirral terraces, we discuss alternative routing options before any work begins.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-who-item pf-who-yes"><span class="pf-who-icon">✓</span><div><strong>Smart thermostat and heating controls</strong><p>A new smart thermostat and programmer installed and set up. Smart controls such as Nest or Hive available on request. Zone controls for larger south Wirral properties available as part of the system design.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-who-item pf-who-yes"><span class="pf-who-icon">✓</span><div><strong>Magnetic system filter</strong><p>A magnetic filter fitted to capture debris and sludge before it reaches the boiler heat exchanger. Required by most boiler manufacturers to maintain warranty validity.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-who-item pf-who-yes"><span class="pf-who-icon">✓</span><div><strong>Inhibitor dosed to BS 7593 standard</strong><p>The system filled with corrosion inhibitor at the correct concentration. A warranty condition for all major boiler manufacturers and essential for long-term system health across Wirral's varied housing stock.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-who-item pf-who-yes"><span class="pf-who-icon">✓</span><div><strong>Full system commissioning and balancing</strong><p>Every radiator balanced individually. System pressure set and a full heating and hot water cycle run before we leave. Your new system works correctly from day one.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-who-item pf-who-yes"><span class="pf-who-icon">✓</span><div><strong>Gas Safe certificate and Benchmark certificate</strong><p>Both issued on the day of completion. The Gas Safe certificate is a legal requirement. The Benchmark certificate registers and validates the boiler warranty with the manufacturer.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-who-item pf-who-yes"><span class="pf-who-icon">✓</span><div><strong>12-month workmanship guarantee</strong><p>All Wirral installations carry a 12-month workmanship guarantee in addition to the manufacturer warranty. If anything fails as a result of our installation work, we return and resolve it at no cost.</p></div></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>


  <!-- ECO4 SECTION -->
  <section class="pf-section" style="background:#f8fafc;">
    <div class="container">
      <h2 style="text-align:center;">ECO4 Grants for Wirral Central Heating</h2>
      <p class="pf-sub">The Wirral is specifically identified as an ECO4-eligible area. Eligible Wirral homeowners may be able to fund part or all of their central heating installation through government schemes. We assess eligibility at the free survey.</p>

      <div class="pf-who-grid" style="margin-top:2rem;">
        <div class="pf-who-item pf-who-yes"><span class="pf-who-icon">✓</span><div><strong>Wirral qualifies as an ECO4 priority area</strong><p>The Wirral is named as a qualifying area under ECO4, meaning that Wirral households may have stronger eligibility than in some other Merseyside areas. We assess your specific eligibility at the free survey and advise on the fastest route to approval.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-who-item pf-who-yes"><span class="pf-who-icon">✓</span><div><strong>ECO4 Scheme. Free central heating for eligible households.</strong><p>Wirral homeowners on qualifying benefits including Universal Credit, Pension Credit or Child Tax Credit, or households with gross income below £31,000, may qualify for a fully funded central heating installation or upgrade under the <a href="https://www.gov.uk/apply-great-british-insulation-scheme" target="_blank" rel="noopener">ECO4 scheme</a>. Properties with EPC ratings of D or below are often eligible.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-who-item pf-who-yes"><span class="pf-who-icon">✓</span><div><strong>Boiler Upgrade Scheme. Up to £7,500 for heat pumps.</strong><p>The <a href="https://www.gov.uk/apply-boiler-upgrade-scheme" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Boiler Upgrade Scheme</a> provides grants of up to £7,500 towards air source heat pump installation. If you are considering a low-carbon alternative for your Wirral property, we advise on suitability at the free survey.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-who-item pf-who-yes"><span class="pf-who-icon">✓</span><div><strong>Finance available for self-funded installations.</strong><p>We work with finance partners to offer flexible payment options for Wirral homeowners who prefer to spread the cost of a full central heating installation. Ask about finance at the free survey. Subject to status and eligibility.</p></div></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>


  <!-- HOW LONG -->
  <section class="pf-section" style="background:#f1f5f9;">
    <div class="container">
      <h2 style="text-align:center;">How Long Does Central Heating Installation Take on the Wirral?</h2>
      <p class="pf-sub">Every Wirral property is different. Here are realistic timelines based on our CH postcode installations.</p>
      <div class="pf-durations" style="margin-top:2rem;">
        <div class="pf-duration-card">
          <div class="pf-duration-time">2-3<br><span style="font-size:0.9rem;">days</span></div>
          <div><strong>Small Wirral flat or 2-bed property. Up to 6 radiators.</strong><p>Common in converted properties in Birkenhead and flats across CH41 to CH45. Straightforward pipe access and a combi boiler setup. Includes boiler, all radiators, controls and commissioning.</p></div>
        </div>
