  <!-- FAQ -->
  <section class="pf-section" style="background:#f1f5f9;">
    <div class="container">
      <h2 style="text-align:center;">Central Heating Installation Wirral. Your Questions Answered</h2>
      <p class="pf-sub">Straight answers to what Wirral homeowners ask most before booking.</p>
      <div class="pf-faq">
        <details class="pf-faq-item"><summary><span class="pf-faq-tag pf-tag-orange">COST</span>&nbsp; How much does central heating installation cost on the Wirral?</summary><div class="pf-faq-body"><p>A full central heating installation on the Wirral starts from £3,500. Checkatrade data places the Wirral average at £4,000 to £6,000 for a 3-bed house. System upgrades start from £1,500. A single radiator addition costs from £200. All prices are confirmed at a free written fixed-price site survey. No surprises on invoice day.</p></div></details>
        <details class="pf-faq-item"><summary><span class="pf-faq-tag pf-tag-navy">COMBI OR SYSTEM</span>&nbsp; What type of boiler does my Wirral property need?</summary><div class="pf-faq-body"><p>It depends on your mains water pressure and the number of bathrooms. Many older Wirral terraces in CH41 to CH45 have mains pressure too low for a combi boiler to deliver satisfactory hot water to an upstairs bathroom. We test mains pressure at every free survey before recommending a system type. Fitting the wrong type is one of the most expensive installation mistakes. We never recommend without testing.</p></div></details>
        <details class="pf-faq-item"><summary><span class="pf-faq-tag pf-tag-orange">ECO4</span>&nbsp; Is ECO4 available for Wirral homeowners?</summary><div class="pf-faq-body"><p>Yes. The Wirral is specifically identified as an ECO4-eligible area. Wirral homeowners on qualifying benefits or with household income below £31,000 may qualify for a fully or partially funded central heating installation. Properties with an EPC rating of D or below are often eligible. We assess eligibility at the free survey at no cost.</p></div></details>
        <details class="pf-faq-item"><summary><span class="pf-faq-tag pf-tag-navy">VICTORIAN</span>&nbsp; Can you install central heating in a Birkenhead or Wallasey Victorian terrace?</summary><div class="pf-faq-body"><p>Yes. Victorian and Edwardian terraces make up a large proportion of our Wirral installations. Solid brick walls, limited floor void access and non-standard layouts all affect pipe routing in these properties. We plan every pipe route at the free survey to preserve original features where possible. We also test mains pressure in every older terrace before recommending a system type.</p></div></details>
        <details class="pf-faq-item"><summary><span class="pf-faq-tag pf-tag-orange">ZONE CONTROL</span>&nbsp; Can you install zone control for my larger Wirral property?</summary><div class="pf-faq-body"><p>Yes. Zone control with separate heating circuits for upstairs and downstairs, or by wing of the property, is common in our larger CH60 to CH64 installations. We design zone systems at the free survey for properties with 10 or more radiators. Zone control with a smart multi-zone thermostat can reduce heating bills by 15 to 25% compared to a single-zone system in a large property.</p></div></details>
        <details class="pf-faq-item"><summary><span class="pf-faq-tag pf-tag-green">GAS SAFE</span>&nbsp; Are you Gas Safe registered for Wirral central heating installation?</summary><div class="pf-faq-body"><p>Yes. All central heating installations across the Wirral are carried out by our own directly employed Gas Safe registered engineers. Verify at <a href="https://www.gassaferegister.co.uk" target="_blank" rel="noopener">gassaferegister.co.uk</a>. We never use sub-contractors.</p></div></details>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>


